A MAN found dead in a Glasgow flat has been named by police.Officers were called to reports of a disturbance in a flat in Benalder Street, Partick, at 8.50am on Saturday and found Scott Gillies seriously injured.The 29-year-old was treated by paramedics but died at the scene.Officers described the death as &quot;suspicious&quot; and launched an investigation.A 23-year-old man was arrested last night in connection with the death.A report will be sent to the procurator fiscal and the man arrested is due to appear at Glasgow Sheriff Court on Monday.Police said a 25-year-old woman was also injured in the incident and is being treated at Glasgow's Western Infirmary.